<TITLE> Scope widens for Hasina's treatment abroad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com) -- Two judges exempted Sheikh Hasina from personally appearing in court in two separate graft cases Monday, while another court also ordered the government to restore the former prime minister's passport, clearing the way for her to travel abroad for better medical treatment. Two special judge's courts, sited on the Sangsad Bhaban complex, exempted the detained Awami League president from a legal binding to appear in person in the barge-mounted power plant and the Niko hearings against her. Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrates Court also ordered the government to return the AL president's passport, which was seized after her arrest and detention a year ago. bdnews
